addr="jms-00BN"
title="Event structure">event structure</fr:link></fr:title><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>10</fr:month><fr:day>26</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:meta
name="source"><fr:link
type="local"
href="staton-winskel-2010.xml"
addr="staton-winskel-2010"
title="On the expressivity of symmetry in event structures">[staton-winskel-2010]</fr:link></fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A <fr:em>configuration</fr:em> of an <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00BN.xml"
addr="jms-00BN"
title="Event structure">event structure</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> is defined to be a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00BP.xml"
addr="jms-00BP"
title="Consistent subsets of an event structure">consistent</fr:link>, downward-closed subset of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex>. We will write <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}_{E}]]></fr:tex> for the set of all configurations of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}_{E}^{\mathit {fin}}]]></fr:tex> for the set of <fr:em>finite</fr:em> configurations of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
